  <description type="morphology">Stems spheric to ovoid, 10–30 × 7.5–20 cm; ribs typically 13, undulate to deeply crenate. Spines 12–16 per areole; central spines 4 per areole, principal central spine strongly flattened, 50–90 × 1.3–3 mm, sometimes ± papery. Flowers 6–7.5 × 7–9 cm; stigma lobes 8–10. Fruits green, yellow-green, or olive, 20–25 × 10–15 mm. Seeds ca. 1 mm.</description>
